explanation: The solution iterates through time, allocating memory to the stick with more available memory until neither stick has enough memory to allocate. It returns the crash time and the remaining memory in both sticks. The time complexity is related to the square root of the maximum initial memory due to the nature of the allocation (1 + 2 + 3 + ... + n = n*(n+1)/2). The space complexity is constant as it only uses a fixed amount of space. The energy implications are low due to the simple iterative nature of the solution.

